freedom and the arts of dissent events at stanford freedom and the arts of dissent facebook twitter email print add to calendar harry camp memorial lecture svetlana boym writer theorist media artist the lecture explores the experience of public freedom as cocreation in the world and miracle of infinite improbability hannah arendt drawing distinctions between liberation and freedom and between estrangement from the world and estrangement for the world the lecture reexamines avant garde and artistic and political dissent in russia and eastern europe of the 20 th century with uncanny connections to the public protests all over the world in 2011 2012 boym explores cross cultural approaches to public freedom and proposes an alternative off modern archeology of the twentieth and twenty first century experimental thought from hannah arendt georg simmel and victor shklovsky to contemporary political art when monday march 19 2012 6 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where humanities center levinthal hall 424 santa teresa street map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends members tags arts lecture reading humanities sponsor humanities center contact 650 725 1219 pmsumana stanford edu admission event is free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 309 30977 more info last modified february 9 2012
